Here's a PHP script that uses cURL to get data from an API using the `API_KEY` value from the environmental variable `PINECONE_API_KEY`:
```php
<?php

// Get API key from environment variable
$apiKey = getenv('PINECONE_API_KEY');

// Set API URL
$url = 'https://api.example.com/data';

// Initialize cURL
$ch = curl_init();

// Set cURL options
curl_setopt($ch, CURLOPT_URL, $url);
curl_setopt($ch, CURLOPT_RETURNTRANSFER, true);
curl_setopt($ch, CURLOPT_HTTPHEADER, array(
  'Authorization: Bearer ' . $apiKey,
));

// Execute cURL request
$result = curl_exec($ch);

// Check for errors
if (curl_errno($ch)) {
  echo 'Error: ' . curl_error($ch);
  exit;
}

// Close cURL
curl_close($ch);

// Output the result
echo $result;

?>
```
Replace `https://api.example.com/data` with the actual API URL you want to use, and make sure to set the appropriate headers and cURL options as needed. The `Authorization` header is set using the `API_KEY` value from the `PINECONE_API_KEY` environmental variable.

